main event: A greenish-white, red-rimmed round object was observed moving northeast at approximately 2,000 feet in the area of Allen, Maryland for 35 minutes on 12th September 1952.
interesting points: The object had a stationary, clear, and green light with white rings.
No targets were detected in the area of the reported sighting using electronic equipment.
The observation was made by a civilian ground observer volunteer and his wife.
The sky was clear with 10 miles visibility at the time of the sighting.
No interception was attempted, and no aircraft were detected by electronic equipment at the station in the area of observation at the time of the sighting.
witnesses: civilian ground observer volunteer and his wife
photographs: yes, the report includes a photograph
